## Objectives

1. Understand how to use if statements to evaluate conditions and execute code based on those conditions.  
2. Learn how to use switch (case) statements for handling multiple options.  
3. Explore for loops to iterate over a series of items.  
4. Practice creating a while loop for repetitive tasks.  
5. Combine these constructs to build a functional Bash script.
